com.bullhornsdk.data.model.entity.association

Class AssociationFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bullhornsdk.data.model.entity.association.AssociationFactory

  • public class AssociationFactory
extends Object
    Central factory class when dealing with entity associations. In most cases client code will only need to deal with this factory class. This class, and the underlying EntityAssociations, ensures type safety and that only valid associations are used when accessing the REST api.
    Author:
    magnus.palm

      • getAssociationField

        public static <T extends AssociationEntity> AssociationField<T,? extends BullhornEntity> getAssociationField(Class<T> type,
                                                                                                             String associationName)
        Returns the AssociationField for the passed in entity type (Candiate, ClientContact etc.), with the association name of the passed in assocationName.

        NOTE: for type safety use candidateAssociations(),categoryAssociations() etc. instead!

        Parameters:
        type -
        associationName -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if no association with the assocationName exists in the type.
